See tips for your level below:
<br>
<br>

 <button class="accordion">Beginner</button>
<div class="panel">
  <p>  You might not know how to draw much yet! It's ok!
    <br>
    1. Find your artsyle.
    <br>
    2. Find what you like to draw (people, objects, nature etc.)
    <br>
    3.Draw a lot!
  </p>
</div>

<button class="accordion">Intermediate</button>
<div class="panel">
  <p>You can draw, but it needs a little more work!
    <br>
    1. KNOW what you like to draw.
    <br>
    2. Practice drawing many different things.
    <br>
    3.Learn anatomy and shadows.(if you haven't already!)
  </p>
</div>

<button class="accordion">Advanced</button>
<div class="panel">
  <p>You know how to draw a lot and with good skill, but you might be looking for more!
    <br>
    1. Master as many skills as you can.
    <br>
    2.Add lots of details
  </p>
</div>
